      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions] Line 355: The new audio-to-video QoS callback fires on every RTCP check while loss remains above 3%, even if audio itself is already adapting. This can repeatedly force video down to minimum bitrate for transient or audio-only loss because there is no hysteresis/recovery signal and the threshold is much higher than the existing video packet-loss threshold. Please add hysteresis or trigger only on sustained congestion, and document/test the expected recovery behavior. Suggested shape:\\n```suggestion\\nif (pondLoss \u003e\u003d AUDIO_CONGESTION_THRESHOLD \u0026\u0026 previousPondLoss_ \u003c AUDIO_CONGESTION_THRESHOLD) {\\n    // signal sustained/edge-triggered congestion\\n}\\n```",
      "revId": "2bd694874bdafd03fa949a202c97757d08a02467",
