      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions] Line 57: The registry stores simulators indefinitely unless tests explicitly call `clear()`/`removeAll()`. Because keys are call IDs, long-running test processes or integration runs can leak simulator instances across calls and produce cross-test contamination. Prefer RAII ownership tied to the call/session lifecycle, or integrate cleanup where calls are torn down.\\n```suggestion\\n// Ensure SIPCall teardown removes all simulators for its call id, or return a scoped handle from getOrCreate().\\n```",
