      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🔴 Critical Issues] Line 635: The simulator silently drops RTCP as well as RTP because it is applied after `isRTCP` detection but before any packet-type filtering. Dropping RTCP feedback changes the control loop itself and can hide or distort the QoS behavior being tested. If the intent is to impair media packets, gate this to RTP only; if RTCP loss is intentional, make it configurable and cover it in tests.\\n```suggestion\\nif (!isRTCP \u0026\u0026 sim \u0026\u0026 !sim-\u003eshouldSend(static_cast\u003csize_t\u003e(buf_size)))\\n    return buf_size;\\n```",
