      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions] Line 636: Returning `buf_size` for a simulated drop makes the sender believe the packet was successfully written, which is fine for loss simulation, but the stats are counted before the actual socket write succeeds. If the subsequent real write fails for non-simulated packets, simulator stats will over-report sent packets. Consider recording successful sends only after `writeData()` succeeds, and only record drops before returning early.",
      "revId": "2bd694874bdafd03fa949a202c97757d08a02467",
