      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions] Line 794: Holding `mutex_` while calling `setupVideoBitrateInfo()` is risky because this method appears to update bitrate state used by the normal video adaptation path; if it acquires the same lock internally or depends on state mutated by `setNewBitrate()`, this can deadlock or race with the RTCP checker. Please verify locking expectations and keep only direct state reads/writes under the lock. A safer pattern is to snapshot the current bitrate info under the lock, compute outside, then call `setNewBitrate()`.",
