      "message": "[🔴 Critical Issues] Line 108: The lab topology does not actually place `BR_A` and `BR_B` on a shared L2 segment or add routes for the peer subnet. Both namespaces are configured as `/24` and will ARP directly for the other peer, but the host-side veth interfaces are separate links, so `peer-a` cannot resolve/reach `10.99.0.2`. The default routes are also ineffective for same-subnet traffic. Use a real Linux bridge with both host veth ends attached, or use point-to-point subnets plus explicit routes.\\n```suggestion\\n# Example direction: create br-qos, attach ${BR_A}/${BR_B}, assign host IP on br-qos,\\n# or configure /30 links and route ${IP_B}/32 via the host-side address.\\n```",
